    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[(Deleted)]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[(Deleted)]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 10</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[After entering R.O.C with a residence visa, the foreign technician employed with permission shall apply for alien residence certificate at the police bureau at the location of residence within 15 days.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 11</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The term of work permit for foreign technicians employed by a construction enterprise is up to 3 years. Where it is necessary to continue employment, the construction enterprise shall submit the following documents within 30 days before expiration of the term to the competent authority to apply for extension of up to 1 year:
1. Letter of application.
2. Four copies of questionnaire for applying for employment of foreign technicians.
3. A copy of employment contract including the contents listed in Subparagraph 4, Paragraph 1, Article 5.
4. Original official document approving employment.
5. Certificates on tax payment during working in R.O.C.
6. Photostat copy of the engineering contract introducing foreign technician. Public works, except environmental protection works that do not use civil engineering as the major contracting works, must be directly contracted. For private construction works, construction license shall be enclosed.
After the extension of the term is approved, the foreign technician shall go to the police at the location of residence to finish the procedure for extended residence.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 12</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where a foreign technician employed in the construction industry is refused to visa, prohibited from entrance or compelled to leave country by related departments, the competent authority shall cancel the employment permit.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 13</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where a foreign technician employed in the construction industry needs to turn over to another employer during the effective term of the employment permit, the new employer shall submit the following documents to the competent authority, and cooperate with the original employer to submit application:
1. Letter of application.
2. Photostat copy of construction enterprise registration certificate.
3. A copy of employment contract including the contents listed in Subparagraph 4, Paragraph 1, Article 5.
4. Original official document approving employment.
5. Dimission certificate produced by the original employer.
6. Certificates on tax payment during working in R.O.C.
7. Photostat copy of the engineering contract introducing foreign technician. Public works, except environmental protection works that do not use civil engineering as the major contracting works, must be directly contracted. For private construction works, construction license shall be enclosed.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 14</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The notice given by a construction enterprise under Article 52 of the Act shall include the name, sex, age, nationality, date of entrance, working term, photo, and serial number of alien residence certificate of the foreign technician.
Upon receipt of the above-mentioned notice, the police departments shall immediately check whether the foreign technician has leaved the country. If not, the case shall be reported to the National Police Agency, Ministry of the Interior to strengthen reconnaissance.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
